ce:section.ce:para:
In order to investigate the band structure of NSO, BVO film and BVO-QDs, Mott-Schottky (MS) and XPS measurements have been employed. MS approach in aqueous environments can imply the flat band potential (Vfb
                        ) of the NSO and BVO film, which is about 0.2eV positive than the conduction band of semiconductor [34]. As shown in Fig. 5c, the Vfb
                         of NSO and BVO film are determined to be 0.456eV and 0.166eV vs. RHE (−0.13eV and −0.42eV vs. Ag/AgCl), which imply the conduction band of NSO and BVO film are 0.256eV and −0.04eV vs. RHE. According to the band gap of NSO (3.7eV) and BVO film (2.5eV), the band structure can be diagramed in Fig. 5d. XPS was employed to investigate the valance band change of the BVO in different particle size [10,35]. As shown in Fig. S7, the valance band edge position of the BVO-QDs and the BVO film was almost the same. Considering the difference in the band gap is about 0.5eV between the QDs and the film, the conduction band edge of BVO-QDs is about −0.5eV vs. RHE (Fig. 5d). Therefore, the photogenerated electrons on BVO-QDs could have enough energy to reduce H+ to H2. In addition, a type II heterojunction has been formed at the interface of NSO and BVO. The electron transfer from BVO to NSO is indeed facilitated.
